'''terrorism'''

# The act of deliberately commiting an act of [[violence]] to create an emotional response from the victim in the furtherance of a [[political]] or social agenda.
# [[Violence]] against civilians to achieve military or [[political]] objectives.

====Derived terms====
*[[bioterrorism]] ''noun''
*[[cyberterrorism]] ''noun''

a psychological strategy of war for gaining political or religious ends by deliberately creating a well-founded climate of fear among the civilian popuation of a state, a society, a race or a people. Such a strategy may be used by an occupying army on the occupied population. Many terrorist acts, especially against an occupying military or against illegal occupants are acts of war or resistance, and not terrorism. The famous saying goes that one mans terrorist is another mans freedom fighter.